Definition: the entire geographical area drained by a river and its tributaries
Example: an area characterized by all runoff being conveyed to the same outlet; flood control in the Missouri basin
Synonyms: basin, watershed, drainage_basin, catchment_area, catchment_basin, drainage_area, geographical_area, the, entire, geographical, area, drained, by, a, river, and, its, tributaries, an, characterized, all, runoff, being, conveyed, to, same, outlet, flood, control, in, Missouri
Category: noun.location
